              <Comments>In some languages there is a very strong negative connotation in any word meaning ‘slave,’ for it may suggest ‘vile person’ or even ‘foreigner,’ since in a number of areas only foreigners were made slaves. It may therefore be necessary to use a term for slave which is more or less equivalent to ‘servant,’ ‘one who works without pay,’ ‘one who must work without pay,’ or ‘bondservant.’</Comments>
